Haters gonna hate. I think Star Wars became the THING to criticize. Audiences developed a hyperbolic love/hate relationship with every release. I'm not going to disprove that, I guess. As a life long Star Wars fan, having been watching the movies for almost 3 decades, I absolutely loved this film. It's extremely fast paced, it's packed with details that probably fly over the heads of fans that aren't aware of extra cinematic content, and it features some controversial choices in narratove, but it absolutely soars as a bookend to the Skywalker Saga. I fell in love with the characters all over again, it featured classic comedic relief from new and old characters, its action sequences are superb, and I left the movie feeling completely satisfied. I've seen it twice, and I'll probably see it again before it leaves theatres. To all of you fans out there, ignore the reviews, go in with a hopeful perspective. And may the force be with you, always.

I went into the movie with an open mind and watched it as a stand alone movie. Overall me and my family enjoyed the movie. As a life long star wars fan there are quite a few gripes I have with the movie but the same can be said of the last two.  I will have to watch it a few more times to really break it down.

It was a fun movie and very intelligently tied up a lot of the loose threads ... which is primarily what the third movie of a trilogy is supposed to do.  At the same time, it left open just enough to begin another sequence sometime in the future.
Fun, Funny, action pack and with a great cast, The rise of Skywalker closes the long saga with just enough satisfaction to forget about the fast pace and confusing story.
